    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-20T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="477"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363/855a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ford</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-20T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 20, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>316. To William Campbell from Marcel Wagner. The number of this message is 0031.
                    We have learned from the Iranian Minister at Washington that his Government has
                    requested him to instruct Curtice and Hoover<note n="64" xml:id="d477fn64">A. A.
                        Curtice and Herbert Hoover, Jr., petroleum geologists, had been commissioned
                        by the Iranian Government as petroleum advisers.</note> who are now the
                    official representatives of the Government of Iran to examine under his auspices
                    in Washington offers of both companies. The Minister has requested that their
                    recommendations be subsequently telegraphed to him. If you can, cable
                    confirmation. [Wagner.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
